<body>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Objective</h2>
    <p>
      To build a low-cost, real-time body monitoring system using an ESP32 Dev Board, 
      a DS18B20 sensor for temperature, and a capacitive moisture sensor for hydration. 
      Data is shown on an OLED display and sent to a mobile device via the Blynk IoT app.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Key Components</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hardware:</strong> ESP32, DS18B20, OLED Display, Breadboard, Jumper wires</li>
      <li><strong>Software:</strong> Arduino IDE, Blynk App</li>
      <li><strong>Libraries:</strong> OneWire, DallasTemperature, Adafruit SSD1306, Adafruit GFX, Blynk</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Working</h2>
    <p>
      ESP32 reads temperature and moisture data, displays them on the OLED, 
      and sends the data to the Blynk app over Wi-Fi.
    </p>
  </div>

</body>
